content:

In the evening ferries will not run. The last service leaves Circular Quay at 7.12pm and Pyrmont at 6.40pm. Services resume with additional late-night ferries leaving Circular Quay at 10.12pm and 11.12pm, and from Pyrmont at 10.40pm and 11.40pm.

urlText: Service changes for Australia Day
content:
Ferries will be affected by exclusion zones on the harbour from 11.45am to 12.30pm and from 7.30pm to 9.45pm while Australia Day events take place on the water on Friday 26 January.
 
Manly ferries will not run during the morning exclusion zone, catch buses to travel between Manly and the city instead, additional route 170x buses will run between Manly and Wynyard. The last ferry leaves Circular Quay at 11.30am and the last ferry leaves Manly at 11.15am. Services resume from Circular Quay at
12.45pm and Manly at 12.30pm.
 
During the evening exclusion zone ferries will not stop at Circular Quay and will use Barangaroo wharf instead. Ferries leaving Manly between 7pm and 9.20pm will stop at Barangaroo. Ferries to Manly between 7.40pm and 9.10pm will leave from Barangaroo instead.
 
Ferries resume running between Manly and Circular Quay from 9.50pm.
 
For more details on ferry service changes and other transport options, visit the Australia Day event page.
